{
  "verses": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "Wine Is a Mocker"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "1",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Wine is a mocker, strong drink is a brawler, and whoever is led astray by them is not wise."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "2",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The terror of a king is like the roar of a lion; whoever provokes him forfeits his own life."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "3",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "It is honorable for a man to resolve a dispute, but any fool will quarrel."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "4",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The slacker does not plow in season; at harvest time he looks, but nothing is there."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "5",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The intentions of a man’s heart are deep waters, but a man of understanding draws them out."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "6",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Many a man proclaims his loving devotion, but who can find a trustworthy man?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "7",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "The righteous man walks with integrity; blessed are his children after him."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "8",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "A king who sits on a throne to judgesifts out all evil with his eyes."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "9",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Who can say,"
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "I have kept my heart pure; I am cleansed from my sin",
          "speaker": "Unknown"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "10",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Differing weights and unequal measures—both are detestable to the LORD."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "11",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Even a young man is known by his actions—whether his conduct is pure and upright."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "12",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Ears that hear and eyes that see—the LORD has made them both."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "13",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Do not love sleep, or you will grow poor; open your eyes, and you will have plenty of food."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "14",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Worthless, worthless!",
          "speaker": "Unknown"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "says the buyer, but on the way out, he gloats."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "15",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "There is an abundance of gold and rubies, but lips of knowledge are a rare treasure."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "16",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Take the garment of the one who posts security for a stranger; get collateral if it is for a foreigner."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "17",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Food gained by fraud is sweet to a man, but later his mouth is full of gravel."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "18",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Set plans by consultation, and wage war under sound guidance."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "19",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He who reveals secrets is a constant gossip; avoid the one who babbles with his lips."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "20",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Whoever curses his father or mother, his lamp will be extinguished in deepest darkness."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "21",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "An inheritance gained quicklywill not be blessed in the end."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "22",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Do not say,"
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "I will avenge this evil!",
          "speaker": "Unknown"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Wait on the LORD, and He will save you."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "23",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Unequal weights are detestable to the LORD, and dishonest scales are no good."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "24",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "A man’s steps are from the LORD, so how can anyone understand his own way?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "25",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "It is a trap for a man to dedicate something rashly, only later to reconsider his vows."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "26",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "A wise king separates out the wicked and drives the threshing wheel over them."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "27",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The spirit of a man is the lamp of the LORD, searching out his inmost being."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "28",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Loving devotion and faithfulness preserve a king; by these he maintains his throne."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "29",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The glory of young men is their strength, and gray hair is the splendor of the old."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "30",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Lashes and wounds scour evil, and beatings cleanse the inmost parts."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    }
  ]
}